11/08/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) police spokesman Radovan Pejic predicted on Wednesday (10 August) that after the arrest of Milan Lukic in Argentina, new surrenders or arrests of individuals wanted by The Hague tribunal might soon follow. At a news conference, Pejic said that contacts and collaboration between RS institutions, Serbia-Montenegro and the international community have intensified. He refused to disclose details of the investigation that led to Lukic's capture, but hinted that RS police had contacted the fugitive's wife and daughter in eastern Sarajevo. (Fena, RTRS - 10/08/05)
